I've heard many different version about legality, and I finally decided myself that download games that have been commercialised more than 5 years ago or so cannot be illegal if there is no new production of the said game, even if this is false. This just seem logical. Some people invokes the argument that emulation could rather lead people to buy more games, but Nintendo looks to disagree. Overall, I found those conclusions. Emulation :<br />- Promote the sales of sequels of earlier games (if you downloaded and liked a game, chances are that you're interested in buying a sequel to if for a more recent game machine)<br />- Doesn't influent much sales of new games<br />- Break down sales of remakes (why buy a remake if you can download the original, wich is often better ?)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Thu Jun 08, 2006 10:50 am</p><hr />
